<font color="#FF0000">THOUGHTS OF EYAH</font><br>
<tt>Thu Aug 21  3:06:59 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Humming Eagle,<br><br>
I fear that I see Eyah in many things. Every tradition seems to have its &quot;Trojan Horse&quot;. To me, the Vietnam War was Eyah because it became very much unlike that which we were led to believe. It was also the vessel in which were carried those things unknown to the experience of most and revealed by transformation into that which we still carry burned into our hearts and minds.<br><br>
I see Eyah as each of us. As I explore myself, there are things within that are revealed by transformation. The White Wolf, the Black Wolf, the primal terror, and the beauty of life, seemingly all at once. Facing that which is in myself is facing Eyah. I acknowledge Eyah. I honor him as a cunning and worthy adversary. I will know him and possess myself. In that way, I will defeat him in terms he will come to understand. In that way, too, I will take care in what I bring into myself, so I may be at peace.<br><br>
Take Care, my Brother of Choice  
